<DOCNO> NYT19980619.0153 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 14:44 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7267 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-STAPLES-COLUMN-TEX     06-19 0625
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STAPLES-COLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DADDY'S GIRLS: TO THEM, HE'S RICH AS COSBY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   One recent Sunday, my daughters were complaining _ again _ that
I never have any money.
</P>
<P>
   And as always when they're done running me down, they offered up
a long list of the attributes that make their father the wonderful
man that he is. Included among those is the fact that he is rich.
As in, say, Bill Cosby rich _ and just as generous and
entertaining.
</P>
<P>
   I shared this little bit of information with a friend recently,
and when she could stop laughing, she told me it reminded her of
her relationship with her father.
</P>
<P>
   ``My father could do no wrong,'' she told me. ``I was definitely
a Daddy's girl. I still am.''
</P>
<P>
   That is how you might describe my daughters, Jamila and Asha. I
don't know when it happened, and so it seems to me that it was
always that way. I birthed them. He stood by with tears in his
eyes. I cook them meals. Jimmy eradicates the nutrients from their
foods. I wash their clothes. He fades them. I discipline. He loves.
</P>
<P>
   I'm certain that my daughters love me, but sometimes I'm green
all over when I consider their relationship with Jimmy. I don't
recall either of them ever crying into the phone for me to come
home, or jumping out of bed to greet me the minute the key turned
in the door. If I miss a goodnight kiss, I have to get it while
they sleep.
</P>
<P>
   Still, I am eternally grateful they love him the way they do,
that they believe in him and trust him to love them.
</P>
<P>
   And I wonder how it is that African-American men like Jimmy are
not known for their good parenting skills, for the way they love
and care for their children.
</P>
<P>
   It is hard to forget the disproportionate number of them who are
behind bars, who make up the unemployment lines. But there are a
great many of these men who, every day, try hard to get it right,
to be there for their children.
</P>
<P>
   I've seen them, and I've talked to them. I've heard the pride in
their voices, seen it on their faces when they talk about their
children. They go to PTA meetings. They attend ballet and piano
recitals. They help with homework and visit the schools. They go on
class field trips and help at school parties.
</P>
<P>
   As I write this, a long chain of faces dances in my memory like
a kite on a string. They smile back at me because they are not just
faces, they are the men I know. They are not perfect, but they are
good and decent like Jimmy.
</P>
<P>
   The other day, while they were visiting me at work, I asked
Jamila and Asha to write part of this column. I asked them to tell
you why they love their father. You should've seen their little
faces light up.
</P>
<P>
   Once we settled on which of them would write first, the typical
childlike responses _ ``He takes me places and he makes me happy''
_ poured forth with the kind of heart and vigor usually witnessed
only on the playground.
</P>
<P>
   ``He buys me things even when I don't ask,'' Asha wrote. ``OH! I
all most forgot. Sometimes he plays with me and he takes me to my
friends' parties and to the movies. He does special things.''
</P>
<P>
   Wrote Jamila: ``I love my dad because he loves me and he takes
care of me. He gives me $20.00 each month. And of all the dads, I
must confess, I think he is the very best.''
</P>
<P>
   I don't dare tell Jamila and Asha that their father isn't rich.
They'll discover that on their own.
</P>
<P>
   What I will try to teach them is that the love and time their
father lavishes on them is what makes THEM rich.
</P>
<P>
   (Gracie Bonds Staples is a columnist for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. Send e-mail to gbs(at)star-telegram.com. Visit the
Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-19-98 1444EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19980619.0154 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 14:45 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7271 &Cx1f; tad-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CHINA-POWER-SIDE-COX-     06-19 0625
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHINA-POWER-SIDE-COX- </SLUG>
