<P>
   TEXAS-DROUGHT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The intense dry spell that has gripped most
of Texas for two months has created a corn, grain sorghum and
cotton disaster in parts of the state, agriculture officials say.
The Texas Agricultural Extension Service estimates that
weather-related losses statewide already have cut farm and ranch
income by more than $500 million this year, and the losses will
likely mount. Typically, agricultural income in Texas ranges from
$13 billion to $15 billion annually. By WORTH WREN JR. Story has
moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-JONES-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Not All Baptists Have a 19th Century Mindset,''
declares a statement sent out by moderate-led Texas Baptists.
``There are millions of Southern Baptists who do not believe women
are second-class citizens ...'' states the declaration. It is part
of the backlash to the Southern Baptist Convention's recent
adoption of a statement that wives are ``to graciously submit to
the servant leadership of their husbands.'' By JIM JONES. Story has
moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTERS-BOMBAY-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Dr. Emilio Bombay rants about the lamentable lack of
knowledge among people who purport to be tech-support staff. By DR.
EMILIO BOMBAY. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   POPS-PSYCHOLOGY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Just in time for Dad's Day, fatherly advice from Homer
Simpson, Hank Hill and Grandpa Pickles. Story will move in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The old adage ``If it ain't broke, don't fix it''
often applies to the world of automotive design, which is why Mazda
took a real chance when it remade the popular Miata roadster for
1999. But I have to agree with the gushing publicity material that
Mazda included with the test vehicle I drove last week. By golly,
they did improve the car, and they didn't mess anything up. By G.
CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STAPLES-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ One Sunday recently, my daughters were complaining
again that I never have money. And as always is the case when
they're done running me down, they offered up this long list of
attributes that make their father the wonderful man that he is.
Included among those is the fact that he is rich. As in, say, Bill
Cosby rich _ and just as generous and entertaining. By GRACIE BONDS
STAPLES. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-HIGH ART &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Seeing Ally Sheedy in ``High Art'' _ and seeing the
way she's used _ is a shock. It's not like watching Judd Nelson
unfurl his nostrils in ``Suddenly Susan,'' where he's the best
thing on the show and he still isn't any good. By ELVIS MITCHELL.
Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
