<HEADLINE>
FATHERLY ADVICE FROM HOMER, HANK AND GRANDPA PICKLES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   He's just a cartoon character, but Hank Hill of the Fox series
``King of the Hill'' knows enough about fatherhood to have written
a book, ``The Boy Ain't Right,'' out just in time for Father's Day.
In it, Hank offers his advice for raising a child _ specifically, a
son, because Hank wouldn't have any idea what to do with a girl.
</P>
<P>
   Yeah, well, other cartoon dads have sons, too, and we wanted to
hear what they had to say, even if we had to make some of it up.
</P>
<P>
   Our panel: Homer Simpson, the well-meaning, beer-swilling,
doughnut-loving doofus from ``The Simpsons''; Grandpa Pickles from
``Rugrats''; Dr. Jonathan Katz, the deadpan psychiatrist from
Comedy Central's ``Dr. Katz''; Duckman, the irresponsibly lecherous
private detective from USA Network's ``Duckman.''
</P>
<P>
   Their wisdom:
</P>
<P>
   Why is the sky blue?
</P>
<P>
   Hank Hill:0BN UMe that's one of the colors of the Dallas Cowboys
uniform.
</P>
<P>
   Homer Simpson: Can't talk _ eating.
</P>
<P>
   Grandpa Pickles: In my day, the sky was bluer than this _ blue
as blue could be.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Katz: Ben, you're 21 years old and all you do is lie around
all day. I'm not entirely convinced that you've ever seen the sky
long enough to determine that it actually ``is'' blue.
</P>
<P>
   Duckman: What are you, Carl Sagan all of a sudden? Shut up and
go watch TV!
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Is there a God?
</P>
<P>
   Hank Hill: Yes _ and he's watching everything you do.
Everything!
</P>
<P>
   Homer Simpson: Oh, yeah. Perfect teeth. Nice smell. A class act
all the way.
</P>
<P>
   Grandpa Pickles: Is the pope Catholic?
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Katz: Yes, and I pray every day that he will give you life.
</P>
<P>
   Duckman: I bet those mindless pod people who believe in that
kind of thing still wait up for the tooth fairy! They shouldn't _
because he's in a Turkish jail!
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Where do babies come from?
</P>
<P>
   Hank Hill: Ask me again when you're 21, Bobby. By that time
you'll be married, and you'll need to know.
</P>
<P>
   Homer Simpson: Bart, you're too young to know that they come
from your mother and I having sex.
</P>
<P>
   Grandpa Pickles: That's a good question, son. Go ask your
mother.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Katz: (Sigh.) Ben, you know those videos you watch all day
... ?
</P>
<P>
   Duckman: ... Uh, hey, Doc, can I borrow some of those videos?
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   What do I do about bullies?
</P>
<P>
   Hank`H`ll: Kick their butts! And come and get me, and I'll kick
their dads' butts!
</P>
<P>
   Homer Simpson: First, you cry like a woman. Then, when he turns
away in disgust, you knock him down. Then, hit him in the back,
kick him in the ribs, and run. I9dpa Pickles: A man's gotta do,
what a man's gotta do.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Katz: Sing this song: ``A boy, a bike, a heart so full/A
mom, a dad, and a little stuffed bull.''
</P>
<P>
   Duckman: Say, ``What the hell are you staring at?'' Then go hide
behind the nearest fat broad.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Can I borrow the car?
</P>
<P>
   Hank Hill: The car's OK, but keep your dang hands off the riding
mower!
</P>
<P>
   Homer Simpson: Do I have to get up? No? Then sure, knock
yourself out.
</P>
<P>
   Grandpa Pickles: Only if you take me with you.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Katz: Ben, you know a lot of the car manufacturers are
offering cars these days in exchange for money people have earned.
</P>
<P>
   Duckman: Uh, sure, just don't look in the trunk or the back
seat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   How do I pick up women?
</P>
<P>
   Hank Hill: Uhhhhhhh ... wouldn't you rather just sell propane
and have them come to you?
</P>
<P>
   Homer Simpson: Pity. Ahhh, sweet pity. Where would my love life
be without it?
</P>
<P>
   Grandpa Pickles: Heh, heh, heh. You've come to the authority on
that one, son.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Katz: Well, you know, Ben, they usually go for guys who are
employed and have their own cars. That would be a start.
</P>
<P>
   Duckman: There's no real technique, it just depends on how hard
you want to get slapped.
</P>
<P>
   _ Robert Philpot, Todd Camp, Kathy Harris and Eric Celeste
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
