<HEADLINE>
1999 MAZDA MIATA ROADSTER
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   At A Glance:
</P>
<P>
   The Package: Subcompact, two-door, two-passenger, four-cylinder,
rear-drive convertible, the all-new second generation of Mazda's
popular little roadster.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: More aggressive, muscular styling, slightly more
power, more rigid body; overall, a very solid upgrade of an already
great car.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Could use an optional, higher-powered engine
(turbocharged?) for more driving fun.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: BMW Z3, Volkswagen Cabrio, Porsche Boxster,
Mercedes-Benz SLK, Mitsubishi Eclipse.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: 25 miles per gallon city, 29 highway.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $19,770 plus $450 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: $22,300, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A-plus.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
