<SLUG> BC-EMLICO-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GE, KEMPER SETTLE EMLICO CLAIMS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By LYNNLEY BROWNING  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Kemper Insurance Companies and General Electric Co.'s
collapsed insurer, known as Emlico, reached an agreement Friday
that settles Kemper's claims against the failed GE unit. The size
and terms of the deal were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   The pact resolved a reinsurance dispute between Kemper and the
Electric Mutual Liability Insurance Co. Ltd. (Emlico), as well as
direct insurance claims between Kemper and GE, according to a joint
statement.
</P>
<P>
   Emlico, founded by GE, is in bankruptcy proceedings after
relocating to Bermuda from Massachusetts in 1995 under a
controversial decision by the state's insurance regulatory body.
GE, a diversified manufacturing, technologies and services company
based in Fairfield, Conn., wants the failed unit to be fully
liquidated in Bermuda. Emlico reinsurers, including Long Grove,
Ill.-based Kemper, have mounted a legal battle to have the
proceedings done in Massachusetts.
</P>
<P>
   Reinsurers are also seeking to limit what may be $2 billion in
cleanup costs related to environmental damage caused by GE at
several areas now deemed Superfund sites.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
