He's tackling the disease headlong, running, swimming and biking
across the U.S. to raise awareness, and funds to fight his disease.
So far, he's raised more than $200,000. Riley's past
accomplishments include racing in 52 triathalons in 52 weeks
beginning on his 52nd birthday. By JUSTIN SCHMID. Story will move
in the ``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   VERGOPIA (Phoenix) _ From all appearances, John Vergopia and his
wife, Dixie Summers, have been living the good life in Scottsdale.
They now sell Arabian horses under the name of En Vogue
International Arabians. But according to a federal indictment
returned against them last week, the couple have been living a lie.
BY JERRY KAMMER. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
