<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEMP-DOWNTURN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEMP AGENCIES HAVING HARD TIME WITH HIRING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY DEBORAH ADAMSON  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ A tight labor market is putting the squeeze on the
hiring efforts of employment agencies.
</P>
<P>
   While a booming economy means more businesses are hiring, it
also means skilled workers are harder to find. That's a dilemma for
the staffing services industry, whose members include Manpower,
Kelly Services, Adecco, AppleOne and On Assignment Inc.
</P>
<P>
   ``It creates a challenge for the staffing services industry to
be able to find people,'' said Bruce Steinberg, spokesman for the
National Association of Temporary and Staffing Services, a trade
group in Alexandria, Va. ``I think that growth will continue to be
constrained by low unemployment.''
</P>
<P>
   Manpower, the biggest U.S. temporary employment company, said
its annual growth has slowed to between 7 percent and 8 percent
from 10 percent to 12 percent. It said the decline is due to a
tight labor market, not from lack of business.
</P>
<P>
   Ron Rudolph, On Assignment's chief financial officer, said
finding job candidates is harder, ``but we're able to fill
positions.''
</P>
<P>
   Shares of most of the publicly traded temporary employment
companies _ including Manpower and On Assignment _ have lost value
on Wall Street as a result of the bleaker forecast. Manpower shares
have fallen 26 percent in the past five trading days, while On
Assignment's have dropped 6.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The low jobless rate prompted AppleOne Employment Services to
take an innovative approach: This spring, it launched its
``Rehirement'' program, which seeks out people with established
careers who are not ready for retirement.
</P>
<P>
   To better find pools of potential job applicants, AppleOne is
opening seven new offices inside Wal-Mart stores this year to add
to about a dozen locations nationwide. None is in Southern
California.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
