Volvo is going topless. The convertible goes on sale early next
month, at a starting price estimated at $44,000. (New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) UNDATED -- June 19, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JUNE 21 --
ABOUT-CARS-VOLVO, 6-19 -- Volvo hopes the C70 coupe will embellish
its safe, staid image. While the C70 is eye-catching and elegant
and its turbo-charged engine serves up some serious fun, it is not
particularly enjoyable to drive. It lacks the sharp reflexes of a
BMW 328is, the rock-of-ages rigidity of a Mercedes CLK320 or the
fist-in-a-velvet-glove control of the Lexus SC 300. (New York Times
Photo)
</P>
