abolish the IRS code. The NFIB has some 600,000 dues-paying firms,
900 employees and an $85 million annual budget. It was ranked this
year as the nation's most powerful business lobby in a survey of
Washington insiders by Fortune magazine. (Photo by George
Bridges/Cox News Service)
