<SLUG> BC-BRAVES-ONDECK20- </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 COX &HT;    On Deck: Montreal Expos
 &HT;    By Jack Wilkinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Olympic Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: TBS, 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP John Smoltz (4-1, 3.94; 10-6,
2.56 lifetime vs. Expos) vs. LHP Carlos Perez (6-5, 3.64; 2-3,
2.98).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Smoltz returns to the rotation tonight after his second
stint on the disabled list and second rehab assignment. After
arthroscopic surgery Dec. 13 to remove bone chips and calcium
deposits from his right elbow, Smoltz came along slowly and
carefully during spring training and began the year on the DL. He
was activated April 15 after an encouraging rehab assignment, and
then won his first four decisions. But after losing 8-1 in Houston
May 17, allowing 10 hits and eight earned runs in just four
innings, Smoltz's next start put him back on the DL with pain in
the elbow. In two-plus innings against the Cubs, he gave up six
hits and two runs. This time, Smoltz made two rehab starts. He went
four innings with Class AA Greenville against Knoxville on June 10,
allowing three hits, including a homer, and two earned runs. On
Sunday with Class A Macon against Capital City, Smoltz worked six
innings, allowing seven hits and four earned runs while throwing 82
pitches and fanning seven.Now he returns. He faces Perez, who
staked himself to an early 1-0 lead in Atlanta last Sunday with a
third-inning homer off Kevin Millwood. But then the Braves pounded
him for seven hits and five runs in the third and fourth innings of
a 5-1 Atlanta win. It was the second loss in a row for Perez after
a personal six-game winning streak. Still, Perez is the only Expos
starter with a winning record, has two of Montreal's three complete
games and averages 7-plus innings per outing, 108 1/3 total in 15
starts.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
