<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-SPOCK-DIET-HEALTH, which moved
in ``a'' news file.) 
  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   If a strict vegetarian diet is part of someone's long-term
culture, the kids grow fine, though not as big. But for those who
became vegans recently, I can't say it's dangerous, but there are
risks.
</P>
<P>
   _ Dr. Mark Jacobson, a specialist in adolescent medicine.
</P>
</TEXT>
